entry.title: [view-transition] Stop BrowserCompositorMac from calling WasShown while
entry.content:
hidden



Calling DelegatedFrameHost::WasShown() while hidden will assign

`first_local_surface_id_after_navigation_` with the LocalSurfaceId

of `BrowserCompositorMac`. This LocalSurfaceId is considered

stale for BFCache restoration with ViewTransition because such

restoration will have customized primary and fallback SurfaceIds.



When the fallback content timer is up, the stale value of

`first_local_surface_id_after_navigation_` will be used to reset the

fallback SurfaceId, which confuses Viz, causing a white screen.



What this CL means:

- As long as we are hidden: HasNoCompositor.

- `SetParentUiLayer` used to be always "successful" because even though

we are hidden, we use UseParentLayerCompositor to represent the state.

With this CL, `SetParentUiLayer` won't re-parent `root_layer_` if we

are hidden. `root_layer_` will be re-parented next time we become

visible (HasNoCompositor->UseParentLayerCompositor).



Bug: 1475903, 1415340

entry.title: [Tab Switcher] Fix possible NPE on HideTabCallback
entry.content:
When the mHideTabCallback was removed, the callbacks passed into

cacheTabThumbnail would invoke run without checking for null.



Fix this by having mHideTabCallback contain the most recent callback

only and then each bitmap fetching callback only contains the instance

of HideTabCallback created for that particular shrink animation. This

avoids the NPE and also prevents incorrectly timed hide calls.

entry.title: Use browser process function to verify password complexity
entry.content:
The set-local-password-input web component needs to check whether a

user-provided password is sufficiently complex. The in-process function

to set a local password also has to perform this check, since otherwise

users would be able to set up weak password by directly calling into the

backend function via devtools.



To have only a single implementation of the complexity check, this

commit makes the set-local-password-input call the in-process function

to check password complexity.

entry.title: Make ChromeDeviceAuthenticatorFactory per profile
entry.content:
This CL is part of a bigger refactoring process of the DeviceAuthenticator class.



The purpose of this CL is to make the ChromeDeviceAuthenticatorFactory

per profile (by creating a proxy which is a profile keyed service). This

change requires to also record the last successful authentication

timestamp per profile (and not have it common for the entire browser

instance, as it was before).



Before, timestamp of last successful authentication was held by

ChromeDeviceAuthenticatorCommon (which extends DeviceAuthenticator) and

was available per browser instance. This timestamp was moved in the

logic of ChromeDeviceAuthenticatorFactory (more specifically, in the

proxy), and it is available per profile.



Before, there was only one ChromeDeviceAuthenticatorCommon instance,

shared using a scoped_ref pointer.

We don't need this anymore, so, in a different CL, we will make it that

every time someone requires a new device authenticator, it will be

created as an unique_ptr and will be connected to the current profile

via the proxy created by the ChromeDeviceAuthenticatorFactory.



Design doc for refactoring: http://docs/document/d/15E8t2BcmN241P-1xpLzYXwROrTzzb1-fS9LnXRnHRKc?resourcekey=0-MgxW9Z7T5rY5AzhcyTg__w#heading=h.xgjl2srtytjt .

entry.title: [PA] Change |FreeNoHooks| to |Free<kNoHooks>|
entry.content:
This is a refactoring change to PA. This change should affect only

inline-ness of |FreeNoHooks| calls in tests.



- Rename |FreeNoHooks| to |FreeInline|

- Rename |FreeNoHooksInUnknownRoot| to |FreeInlineInUnknownRoot|

- Add |FreeFlags::kNoHooks|

- Allow using |kNoHooks| in |Free***|

- There should be no overhead because all conditional branching is

performed at compile-time.

- Rewrite all |FreeNoHooks| usage to:

- |Free| if in tests

- |FreeInline| otherwise

- Rewrite all |FreeNoHooksInUnknownRoot| usage to:

- |FreeInUnknownRoot| if in tests

- |FreeInlineInUnknownRoot| otherwise



Context:

Historically |FreeNoHooks| existed to make hook-less allocation

faster by omitting some conditional branching based on allocation

flags. However, https://crrev.com/c/4722182 constexpr-nized flags

so there is no performance overhead.

Making it private makes allocation flow and PA's API more simple.

entry.title: Privatize content features.
entry.content:
There are two headers to declare features in content.

- the public one: `content/public/common/content_features.h`

- the private one: `content/common/features.h`.



Unfortunately, most are declared in the public one, despite being used

privately exclusively. This violate the `content/public/` rules. This

patches provides a fix.



Parts of this patch was made programmatically using this script:

https://paste.googleplex.com/6699322946093056, with the following

output: https://paste.googleplex.com/5591288895242240



This patch:

1. Update `docs/how_to_add_your_feature_flag.md` to incentive

developers to the non public versions.

2. Move ~70 features back into the private version.

3. Programmatically update the includes to include the correct

#include header(s).

4. For consistency and minimizing the amount of files modified,

the two headers to use the `features::` namespace.

entry.title: Prerender2: prospective fix for keyboard input hangs when IME is present
entry.content:
This is a prospective fix for Chrome on macOS not responsive for

keyboard inputs iff all the below conditions hold:

- The page was Prerender2-ed and activated successfully,

- IME is enabled, and

- RenderWidgetHostViewMac::GetCachedFirstRectForCharacterRange

fast-path could not be used.



Under this condition, somehow (suggests Mojo capability control bug?)

`TextInputHost().GotFirstRectForRange()` call [1] doesn't make it to

the browser UI thread, failing to unblock it waiting until 1500ms

timeout kicks in. [2]



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/local_frame_mojo_handler.cc;drc=71d3885ad42265ebd0f9b09fa1eb074314f25123;l=980

[2] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:content/browser/renderer_host/text_input_client_mac.mm;l=108;drc=2a783dc765bc26cb7387dfff16bdf65fa4ecd9ca



This CL attempts to fix the issue by allowlisting the TextInputHost

mojom interface in the mojo capabilities control.

Original change's description:

> media/gpu/test: Fix H.264 NALU boundary detection

>

> video_decode_accelerator_(perf_)test's EncodedDataHelper is used for

> reading H.264 (and other codecs ofc) bitstreams frames from disk. To

> find the NALU boundary, it looks for the marker 0x00 00 00 01; however,

> NALUs can also be marked by 0x00 00 01 (*); this CL fixes this.

>

> This situation was found during V4L2StatefulVideoDecoder bringup: it

> was observed that said decoder was fed very large media::DecoderBuffers

> for some H.264 specific "main" test vectors (e.g. CAPCM1_Sand_E.h264)

> and this was traced down to EncodedDataHelper not reading one NALU at

> a time from disk, but bundling very many at once.

>

> With this CL, all H.264 main test vectors verify MD5Sums on trogdor

> _except_ for CVPCMNL2_SVA_C.h264 (argh! :).

>

> (*) This is described in the spec but a quick search gives as well e.g.

> https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/directshow/h-264-video-types#h264-bitstream-with-start-codes

entry.title: CrOS Settings: Fix Battery Saver toggle disable
entry.content:
Battery Saver can not be enabled while on AC power. But the existing

code just checks that power sources exist and that they are not USB.



Some USB-C hubs advertise that they are power sources even when not

providing power, disabling the battery saver toggle in settings when

e.g. plugged into a monitor but not charging.



This CL switches the settings UI to use the same logic as

BatterySaverController: is the power source AC?



Bug: b:296300871

Test: Connect a CableMatters 201046_V dongle with nothing else

connected, see that the battery saver toggle in power settings is not

disabled.

entry.title: Use the standard-compliant forbidden character '^' as an invalid URL
entry.content:
Currently, in the rewriting rule of the test runners, "~NOTFOUND" is

used as an invalid URL. However, '~' is NOT a forbidden character

according to the URL standard.



Chromium is addressing [1] this non-compliant behavior and will permit

'~' character in URL hosts. Thus, we can no longer use "~NOTFOUND" as

it will become a valid URL.



As an alternative, any invalid character is acceptable. Let's use '^'

because '^' is a forbidden character both before and after the CL [1].



The PR for WPT Chrome runner is:

https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt/pull/41840/



[1]: https://crrev.com/c/4823237
